# Sadgi Design System Rules

The project already contains an established design system installed via:
`npx getdesign@latest add cursor`

This design system is mandatory. All implementation must follow it exactly.

- Do not regenerate components.
- Do not replace components.
- Do not redesign layouts.
- Do not introduce external UI patterns.
- Extend existing components only where necessary.
- No visual decisions are to be made during implementation.

The existing design system defines:
- typography
- spacing
- layout
- animation
- interaction
- accessibility
- components
- icons
- color tokens

Implementation must reuse these without modification.
If a component is missing, create it following the established design language.
No external inspiration is permitted.

The design system has absolute priority over generated code.

## Quality Checklist
Every implementation must satisfy this checklist before completion:
- [ ] Uses existing color tokens
- [ ] Uses existing typography
- [ ] Uses existing spacing
- [ ] Uses existing shadows
- [ ] Uses existing motion
- [ ] Uses existing buttons
- [ ] Uses existing cards
- [ ] Uses existing icons
- [ ] Uses existing layouts
- [ ] Uses existing accessibility patterns

If any answer is NO, stop implementation and refactor until every answer is YES.
